        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    Work out the square of:
                </p>
                <p>
                    <ol marker="a)">
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                <m>\frac{2}{5}</m>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    <ol marker="a)">
                        <li>
                            <p><m>\left( \frac{2}{5} \right)^2</m></p>
                            <p>To square a fraction, square both the numerator (top number) and the denominator (bottom number). <m>\left( \frac{2}{5} \right)^2 = \frac{2^2}{5^2}</m></p>
                            <p>Square the numerator: <m>2^2 = 2 \times 2 = 4</m></p>
                            <p>Square the denominator: <m>5^2 = 5 \times 5 = 25</m></p>
                            <p>Combine the squared numerator and denominator to form the new fraction.</p>
                            <p><m>\left( \frac{2}{5} \right)^2 = \frac{2^2}{5^2} = \frac{4}{25}</m></p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </solution>
        </example>
        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    Work out the following:
                </p>
                <p>
                    <ol marker="a)"> 
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                <m>\left(2 \frac{2}{7}\right)^2</m>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    <m>\left(2 \frac{2}{7}\right)^2</m>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Convert the mixed fraction to an improper fraction. 
                </p>
                <p>
                    <me>2\frac{2}{7} = \frac{(7 \times 2) + 2}{7}= \frac{16}{7}</me>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Find the square of the improper fraction by squaring both the numerator and denominator.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow>\left(\frac{16}{7}\right)^2 = \frac{16^2}{7^2} \amp = \frac{16 \times 16}{7 \times 7}</mrow>
                        <mrow> \amp = \frac{256}{49} </mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Convert the improper fraction <m>\frac{256}{49}</m> to a mixed fraction.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow>\frac{256}{49}  \amp = 5 \frac{11}{49} </mrow>
                        <mrow></mrow>
                        <mrow> \amp = 5 \frac{11}{49} </mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
            </solution>
        </example>
